result.formatted_address: 210 Temple St, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.name: Temple Street Spicy Crabs

reviews.text: The ambience. Locals and expats enjoying beers and seafood even the weather is hot or raining. And in 5 seconds there is this local night market which is convenient though a bit expensive. Some Chinese vendors get rude when don't buy their stuff after asking the price- too impatient. But overall it's a good local feel

Close to obnoxious service. Very basic seating, atmosphere and told to move on from the table where we sat even through few customers were about. Used to have seating on the main street but seems a new city ordinance prevents that now. Proof that the brand as Asia's World City and the real experience can be patchy. Ah well, makes other restaurant experiences relatively more enjoyable.

I love crabs and I know the one I had was fresh, it didn't stick to the shell and the texturr was nice. If you like your food spicy take the spicy crab you won't regret it. 200 hkd for a crab is a bit pricey but it was worth it. 
We also took some noodles and clams that were fairly good. 
The meat dish we had more mushrooms than meat. 
Loved the corn, a bit oily but I didn't care. 
The staff seems a bit lost when it comes to orders and they are not very polite. I saw one of the staff asking a family to leave because they finished, but there was some space left for new customers.
Don't go there if you want to eat in a clean restaurant. The seats are pretty much like any basic asian restaurants, not very comfy.
Would I come back there if I come back to Hong Kong? Maybe, but I think I'd try another place for crabs
Food was fine.  Don't have to go to the loo, you'll be sent far away and down an ally

This restaurant is eye catchy as it occupies a corner & 2 units across the streets. Many tourists patronise it due to convenience. Food sucks & is heavily spiced to cover up for the un-freshness. I ordered stirred fried garlic crab but the crab is heavily peppered !! The crab meat stick to the shell, which proves that the crab is no good.👎👎👎. The meat is hard & taste saltish & full of pepper. For HK$200 for a crab, it’s expensive & I would at least expect something more decent. Don’t expect much about the environment of the restaurant. It’s eat fast & get out fast.

result.adr_address: G/F, 105 Woosung St, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: G/F, 105 Woosung St, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.name: Ming Fat Cafe Restaurant

reviews.text:
Interesting story, hopefully the right place, spicy crab place on the corner opposite 7/11.
We had one beer and a small spicy clam dish. Only one third of the clams had something inside, the others were all empty. When we went to pay, we offered the amount less the beer as a fair price for the lack of clams situation. She took the money, threw the clams onto the street and picked up the empty beer bottle and tried to smash it on the table and yelled abuse at us :). My husband had to intervene to save me from the crazy lady (most likely a multiple cat owner). Experience 5/5, customer service 0 but I had to give it some star rating.

2019/6月に再訪
以前はシャコや大きなカニなど、比較的高価な時価のメニューばかり頼んでいたので500ドル〜でしたが、最近はもっとリーズナブルなものにシフトし、だいたい300ドル前後のお会計です。リーズナブルとはいえどれも美味しいです。お値段の参考まで。

香港に行くと毎回決まって初日に行きます。にんにくのたっぷりきいた海鮮料理が最高です。オープンエアーの暑い中で海鮮と共に飲むビール最高です。値段もお手頃で、2人で好き放題飲んで食べて500〜700ドルくらいです。写真付きのメニューもありオーダーも簡単です。店員さんも一見ぶっきらぼうかに見えてとても親切です。時価のメニューなど値段を聞くと紙に書いて教えてくれます。ただ、清潔感を重視する方にはおすすめできないかなと思います。

템플스트릿에서 스파이시 크랩 요리 찾으시면 이 집 추천 드립니다!!!! 보통 2마리에 더 저렴하게 파는데 1마리로도 따로 팔아요(가격은 싯가에 따라 다름) 2인이서 다른 요리 곁들여 먹기에 충분했고 진심 불맛에 바삭하고 고소하고 맛있었습니다. 같이 간 일행이 해산물을 즐기는 편이 아닌데도 맥주 안주로 딱이라며 허겁지겁 먹더라구요. 맛조개 요리도 정말 맛있습니다 ㅋㅋ 밥 시켜서 비벼 드세요 ㅋㅋㅋㅋㅋㅋ (참고로 공심채 요리는 좀 심심했습니다)

Very awesome tasty. Amazing spicy crab, seashell with soybean squce!! Very recommended. We really enjoy those foods with beer. I want to go there again to eat Spicy crab!!
나쁘지않다. 맥주와함께하면좋은 맛!
